28bool UseCoarseFilterResetHangover() {
29 return !field_trial::IsEnabled(
30 "WebRTC-Aec3CoarseFilterResetHangoverKillSwitch");
31}
32
33void PredictionError(const Aec3Fft& fft,
34 const FftData& S,
35 rtc::ArrayView<const float> y,
36 std::array<float, kBlockSize>* e,
37 std::array<float, kBlockSize>* s) {
38 std::array<float, kFftLength> tmp;
39 fft.Ifft(S, &tmp);
40 constexpr float kScale = 1.0f / kFftLengthBy2;
41 std::transform(y.begin(), y.end(), tmp.begin() + kFftLengthBy2, e->begin(),
42 [&](float a, float b) { return a - b * kScale; });
43
44 if (s) {
45 for (size_t k = 0; k < s->size(); ++k) {
46 (*s)[k] = kScale * tmp[k + kFftLengthBy2];
47 }
48 }
49}
50
51void ScaleFilterOutput(rtc::ArrayView<const float> y,
52 float factor,
53 rtc::ArrayView<float> e,
54 rtc::ArrayView<float> s) {
55 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(y.size(), e.size());
56 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(y.size(), s.size());
57 for (size_t k = 0; k < y.size(); ++k) {
58 s[k] *= factor;
59 e[k] = y[k] - s[k];
60 }
61}

65Subtractor::Subtractor(const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
66 size_t num_render_channels,
67 size_t num_capture_channels,
68 ApmDataDumper* data_dumper,
69 Aec3Optimization optimization)
70 : fft_(),
71 data_dumper_(data_dumper),
72 optimization_(optimization),
73 config_(config),
74 num_capture_channels_(num_capture_channels),
75 use_coarse_filter_reset_hangover_(UseCoarseFilterResetHangover()),
76 refined_filters_(num_capture_channels_),
77 coarse_filter_(num_capture_channels_),
78 refined_gains_(num_capture_channels_),
79 coarse_gains_(num_capture_channels_),
80 filter_misadjustment_estimators_(num_capture_channels_),
81 poor_coarse_filter_counters_(num_capture_channels_, 0),
82 coarse_filter_reset_hangover_(num_capture_channels_, 0),
83 refined_frequency_responses_(
84 num_capture_channels_,
85 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>(
86 std::max(config_.filter.refined_initial.length_blocks,
87 config_.filter.refined.length_blocks),
88 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>())),
89 refined_impulse_responses_(
90 num_capture_channels_,
91 std::vector<float>(GetTimeDomainLength(std::max(
92 config_.filter.refined_initial.length_blocks,
93 config_.filter.refined.length_blocks)),
94 0.f)) {
95 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < num_capture_channels_; ++ch) {
96 refined_filters_[ch] = std::make_unique<AdaptiveFirFilter>(
97 config_.filter.refined.length_blocks,
98 config_.filter.refined_initial.length_blocks,
99 config.filter.config_change_duration_blocks, num_render_channels,
100 optimization, data_dumper_);
101
102 coarse_filter_[ch] = std::make_unique<AdaptiveFirFilter>(
103 config_.filter.coarse.length_blocks,
104 config_.filter.coarse_initial.length_blocks,
105 config.filter.config_change_duration_blocks, num_render_channels,
106 optimization, data_dumper_);
107 refined_gains_[ch] = std::make_unique<RefinedFilterUpdateGain>(
108 config_.filter.refined_initial,
109 config_.filter.config_change_duration_blocks);
110 coarse_gains_[ch] = std::make_unique<CoarseFilterUpdateGain>(
111 config_.filter.coarse_initial,
112 config.filter.config_change_duration_blocks);
113 }
114
115 RTC_DCHECK(data_dumper_);
116 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < num_capture_channels_; ++ch) {
117 for (auto& H2_k : refined_frequency_responses_[ch]) {
118 H2_k.fill(0.f);
119 }
120 }
121}
122
123Subtractor::~Subtractor() = default;
124
125void Subtractor::HandleEchoPathChange(
126 const EchoPathVariability& echo_path_variability) {
127 const auto full_reset = [&]() {
128 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < num_capture_channels_; ++ch) {
129 refined_filters_[ch]->HandleEchoPathChange();
130 coarse_filter_[ch]->HandleEchoPathChange();
131 refined_gains_[ch]->HandleEchoPathChange(echo_path_variability);
132 coarse_gains_[ch]->HandleEchoPathChange();
133 refined_gains_[ch]->SetConfig(config_.filter.refined_initial, true);
134 coarse_gains_[ch]->SetConfig(config_.filter.coarse_initial, true);
135 refined_filters_[ch]->SetSizePartitions(
136 config_.filter.refined_initial.length_blocks, true);
137 coarse_filter_[ch]->SetSizePartitions(
138 config_.filter.coarse_initial.length_blocks, true);
139 }
140 };
141
142 if (echo_path_variability.delay_change !=
143 EchoPathVariability::DelayAdjustment::kNone) {
144 full_reset();
145 }
146
147 if (echo_path_variability.gain_change) {
148 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < num_capture_channels_; ++ch) {
149 refined_gains_[ch]->HandleEchoPathChange(echo_path_variability);
150 }
151 }
152}
153
154void Subtractor::ExitInitialState() {
155 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < num_capture_channels_; ++ch) {
156 refined_gains_[ch]->SetConfig(config_.filter.refined, false);
157 coarse_gains_[ch]->SetConfig(config_.filter.coarse, false);
158 refined_filters_[ch]->SetSizePartitions(
159 config_.filter.refined.length_blocks, false);
160 coarse_filter_[ch]->SetSizePartitions(config_.filter.coarse.length_blocks,
161 false);
162 }
163}
164
165void Subtractor::Process(const RenderBuffer& render_buffer,
166 const std::vector<std::vector<float>>& capture,
167 const RenderSignalAnalyzer& render_signal_analyzer,
168 const AecState& aec_state,
169 rtc::ArrayView<SubtractorOutput> outputs) {
170 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_capture_channels_, capture.size());
171
172 // Compute the render powers.
173 const bool same_filter_sizes = refined_filters_[0]->SizePartitions() ==
174 coarse_filter_[0]->SizePartitions();
175 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1> X2_refined;
176 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1> X2_coarse_data;
177 auto& X2_coarse = same_filter_sizes ? X2_refined : X2_coarse_data;
178 if (same_filter_sizes) {
179 render_buffer.SpectralSum(refined_filters_[0]->SizePartitions(),
180 &X2_refined);
181 } else if (refined_filters_[0]->SizePartitions() >
182 coarse_filter_[0]->SizePartitions()) {
183 render_buffer.SpectralSums(coarse_filter_[0]->SizePartitions(),
184 refined_filters_[0]->SizePartitions(),
185 &X2_coarse, &X2_refined);
186 } else {
187 render_buffer.SpectralSums(refined_filters_[0]->SizePartitions(),
188 coarse_filter_[0]->SizePartitions(), &X2_refined,
189 &X2_coarse);
190 }
191
192 // Process all capture channels
193 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < num_capture_channels_; ++ch) {
194 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kBlockSize, capture[ch].size());
195 SubtractorOutput& output = outputs[ch];
196 rtc::ArrayView<const float> y = capture[ch];
197 FftData& E_refined = output.E_refined;
198 FftData E_coarse;
199 std::array<float, kBlockSize>& e_refined = output.e_refined;
200 std::array<float, kBlockSize>& e_coarse = output.e_coarse;
201
202 FftData S;
203 FftData& G = S;
204
205 // Form the outputs of the refined and coarse filters.
206 refined_filters_[ch]->Filter(render_buffer, &S);
207 PredictionError(fft_, S, y, &e_refined, &output.s_refined);
208
209 coarse_filter_[ch]->Filter(render_buffer, &S);
210 PredictionError(fft_, S, y, &e_coarse, &output.s_coarse);
211
212 // Compute the signal powers in the subtractor output.
213 output.ComputeMetrics(y);
214
215 // Adjust the filter if needed.
216 bool refined_filters_adjusted = false;
217 filter_misadjustment_estimators_[ch].Update(output);
218 if (filter_misadjustment_estimators_[ch].IsAdjustmentNeeded()) {
219 float scale = filter_misadjustment_estimators_[ch].GetMisadjustment();
220 refined_filters_[ch]->ScaleFilter(scale);
221 for (auto& h_k : refined_impulse_responses_[ch]) {
222 h_k *= scale;
223 }
224 ScaleFilterOutput(y, scale, e_refined, output.s_refined);
225 filter_misadjustment_estimators_[ch].Reset();
226 refined_filters_adjusted = true;
227 }
228
229 // Compute the FFts of the refined and coarse filter outputs.
230 fft_.ZeroPaddedFft(e_refined, Aec3Fft::Window::kHanning, &E_refined);
231 fft_.ZeroPaddedFft(e_coarse, Aec3Fft::Window::kHanning, &E_coarse);
232
233 // Compute spectra for future use.
234 E_coarse.Spectrum(optimization_, output.E2_coarse);
235 E_refined.Spectrum(optimization_, output.E2_refined);
236
237 // Update the refined filter.
238 if (!refined_filters_adjusted) {
239 // Do not allow the performance of the coarse filter to affect the
240 // adaptation speed of the refined filter just after the coarse filter has
241 // been reset.
242 const bool disallow_leakage_diverged =
243 coarse_filter_reset_hangover_[ch] > 0 &&
244 use_coarse_filter_reset_hangover_;
245
246 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1> erl;
247 ComputeErl(optimization_, refined_frequency_responses_[ch], erl);
248 refined_gains_[ch]->Compute(X2_refined, render_signal_analyzer, output,
249 erl, refined_filters_[ch]->SizePartitions(),
250 aec_state.SaturatedCapture(),
251 disallow_leakage_diverged, &G);
252 } else {
253 G.re.fill(0.f);
254 G.im.fill(0.f);
255 }
256 refined_filters_[ch]->Adapt(render_buffer, G,
257 &refined_impulse_responses_[ch]);
258 refined_filters_[ch]->ComputeFrequencyResponse(
259 &refined_frequency_responses_[ch]);
260
261 if (ch == 0) {
262 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_subtractor_G_refined", G.re);
263 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_subtractor_G_refined", G.im);
264 }
265
266 // Update the coarse filter.
267 poor_coarse_filter_counters_[ch] =
268 output.e2_refined < output.e2_coarse
269 ? poor_coarse_filter_counters_[ch] + 1
270 : 0;
271 if (poor_coarse_filter_counters_[ch] < 5) {
272 coarse_gains_[ch]->Compute(X2_coarse, render_signal_analyzer, E_coarse,
273 coarse_filter_[ch]->SizePartitions(),
274 aec_state.SaturatedCapture(), &G);
275 coarse_filter_reset_hangover_[ch] =
276 std::max(coarse_filter_reset_hangover_[ch] - 1, 0);
277 } else {
278 poor_coarse_filter_counters_[ch] = 0;
279 coarse_filter_[ch]->SetFilter(refined_filters_[ch]->SizePartitions(),
280 refined_filters_[ch]->GetFilter());
281 coarse_gains_[ch]->Compute(X2_coarse, render_signal_analyzer, E_refined,
282 coarse_filter_[ch]->SizePartitions(),
283 aec_state.SaturatedCapture(), &G);
284 coarse_filter_reset_hangover_[ch] =
285 config_.filter.coarse_reset_hangover_blocks;
286 }
287
288 coarse_filter_[ch]->Adapt(render_buffer, G);
289 if (ch == 0) {
290 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_subtractor_G_coarse", G.re);
291 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_subtractor_G_coarse", G.im);
292 filter_misadjustment_estimators_[ch].Dump(data_dumper_);
293 DumpFilters();
294 }
295
296 std::for_each(e_refined.begin(), e_refined.end(),
297 [](float& a) { a = rtc::SafeClamp(a, -32768.f, 32767.f); });
298
299 if (ch == 0) {
300 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_refined_filters_output", kBlockSize,
301 &e_refined[0], 16000, 1);
302 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_coarse_filter_output", kBlockSize,
303 &e_coarse[0], 16000, 1);
304 }
305 }
306}
307
308void Subtractor::FilterMisadjustmentEstimator::Update(
309 const SubtractorOutput& output) {
310 e2_acum_ += output.e2_refined;
311 y2_acum_ += output.y2;
312 if (++n_blocks_acum_ == n_blocks_) {
313 if (y2_acum_ > n_blocks_ * 200.f * 200.f * kBlockSize) {
314 float update = (e2_acum_ / y2_acum_);
315 if (e2_acum_ > n_blocks_ * 7500.f * 7500.f * kBlockSize) {
316 // Duration equal to blockSizeMs * n_blocks_ * 4.
317 overhang_ = 4;
318 } else {
319 overhang_ = std::max(overhang_ - 1, 0);
320 }
321
322 if ((update < inv_misadjustment_) || (overhang_ > 0)) {
323 inv_misadjustment_ += 0.1f * (update - inv_misadjustment_);
324 }
325 }
326 e2_acum_ = 0.f;
327 y2_acum_ = 0.f;
328 n_blocks_acum_ = 0;
329 }
330}
331
332void Subtractor::FilterMisadjustmentEstimator::Reset() {
333 e2_acum_ = 0.f;
334 y2_acum_ = 0.f;
335 n_blocks_acum_ = 0;
336 inv_misadjustment_ = 0.f;
337 overhang_ = 0.f;
338}
339
340void Subtractor::FilterMisadjustmentEstimator::Dump(
341 ApmDataDumper* data_dumper) const {
342 data_dumper->DumpRaw("aec3_inv_misadjustment_factor", inv_misadjustment_);
343}
